- v1.0.4 | Mar 16 2026:

  [Fix] All bare rm/mv/cp calls (23 sites) now use `command` prefix — bypasses
        interactive aliases on systems where ~/.bashrc sets -i flags
  [Fix] geoip_cidr_search: reject IPv6 input and non-IPv4 strings that previously
        produced silent wrong results via AWK integer evaluation
  [Fix] geoip_ip_lookup: reject non-numeric dotted-quad strings at bash level
  [Change] _geoip_download_cmd: gate TLS insecure fallback on certificate-specific
           exit codes only (curl 35/51/60/77, wget 5) instead of any failure;
           prevents insecure retry on non-TLS errors (connection refused, timeout, DNS)
  [New] GEOIP_TLS_INSECURE env var — set to "1" to force insecure TLS fallback on
        any failure (escape hatch for edge-case legacy systems)
  [Change] basename in loops replaced with parameter expansion; cat replaced
           with read builtin in geoip_is_stale
  [Change] geoip_validate_cc docstring clarifies format-only validation semantics

- v1.0.2 | Mar 14 2026:

  [New] _GEOIP_V6_AWK — shared mawk-safe awk v6hex() normalizes any IPv6
        address to 32-char lowercase hex; rejects dotted-quad mapped addresses
  [New] _geoip_cidr6_to_ranges() — convert IPv6 CIDR file to hex-range format
        with non-nibble-aligned prefix masking; skips mapped IPv4 CIDRs
  [New] geoip_ip6_lookup() — IPv6 address to country code lookup via 32-char
        hex string comparison (no 128-bit arithmetic); rejects IPv4 and
        dotted-quad mapped addresses
  [New] geoip_build_ip6db() — build consolidated IPv6 hex-range database from
        per-country cascade downloads (~240 serial requests, ~2-5 min);
        LC_ALL=C sort for locale-safe hex ordering; default min_ranges=500

- v1.0.1 | Mar 12 2026:

  [New] geoip_all_cc() — enumerate all known country codes from continent variables
  [New] geoip_ip_lookup() — IPv4 address to country code lookup in integer-range database
  [New] geoip_build_ipdb() — build consolidated IPv4 integer-range database from
        ipdeny.com bulk tarball with per-country cascade fallback
  [Fix] geoip_all_cc: avoid IFS contamination when caller has unset IFS

- v1.0.0 | Mar 12 2026:

  [Fix] _geoip_download_ipverse/_geoip_download_ipdeny: handle mv failure — return 1 and clean up tmpfile
  [Fix] geoip_download: validate CC format (2-letter alpha only) to prevent path traversal in URLs
  [Fix] _geoip_download_cmd: add curl -f (fail on HTTP errors) and -L (follow redirects) flags
  [New] _geoip_download_cmd() — curl/wget download with TLS fallback for CentOS 6 compat
  [New] _geoip_download_ipverse() — ipverse.net CIDR download with content validation
  [New] _geoip_download_ipdeny() — ipdeny.com CIDR download with content validation
  [New] geoip_download() — multi-vendor cascade (ipverse then ipdeny), per-CC CIDR download
  [New] geoip_is_stale() — .last_update age check with configurable max_age_days
  [New] geoip_mark_updated() — write epoch timestamp to .last_update
  [New] geoip_cidr_search() — portable AWK IPv4 CIDR containment (from APF geoip.apf)
  [New] _geoip_validate_cidr_file() — CIDR content validation to prevent cache poisoning
  [New] Binary discovery at source time (GEOIP_CURL_BIN, GEOIP_WGET_BIN, GEOIP_AWK_BIN)
  [New] GEOIP_DL_TIMEOUT configurable via env (default 120s)
  [Fix] Remove dead shellcheck disable=SC2154 on source guard
  [Fix] Add inline comment on 2>/dev/null at source guard per project convention
  [Fix] Fix test title "57+ CCs" to match assertion threshold (>= 54)
  [New] Standalone geoip_lib repository extracted from APF geoip metadata functions
  [New] geoip_cc_name() — ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 to country name mapping (~180 countries)
  [New] geoip_cc_continent() — country code to continent shorthand (@AF/@AS/@EU/@NA/@SA/@OC)
  [New] geoip_continent_name() — continent shorthand to full name (Africa, Asia, etc.)
  [New] geoip_expand_codes() — continent shorthand to comma-separated CC list expansion
  [New] geoip_validate_cc() — CC or @XX validation with type/codes output variables
  [New] Module-level continent CC lists defined once, eliminating APF's duplication
  [New] Eval-free continent lookup via case-based comma search (replaces APF's eval)
  [New] Source guard for safe repeated sourcing
  [New] BATS test suite with batsman CI (9-OS matrix)
